article.headline: Indiana 79, North Texas 70
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Bracey Wright scored 39 points, 28 before halftime, and Indiana led throughout in a 79-70 win over North Texas on Monday night. Wright scored Indiana's first eight points, putting the Hoosiers (6-4) ahead 8-2 with two 3-pointers and another jumper in the first 90 seconds. One of those 3-pointers was the first basket of the game. Wright was 9-of-15 shooting, including six-of-seven 3-pointers. The sophomore also led the Hooisers with seven rebounds and five assists. One of Wright's 3-pointer put Indiana ahead 23-8 with 12:50 left. Another long-range basket 7{ minutes later created the biggest lead, 39-21. North Texas (4-6) got to 69-64 when Shawnson Johnson hit two free throws with 3:30 left. But Wright then hit two free throws and Ryan Tapack made a 3-pointer to stretch the lead back to 10. Johnson led the Mean Green with 21 points and 11 rebounds. Jerome Rogers and Michael Jones both had 10 points. A.J. Moye had 11 points and Sean Kline 10 for Indiana.
